</div>
</div>
<p>
If you want to learn more about human hybrids, click on the links listed at right. As indicated by the reliability arrow, the various types of human-animal hybrids in the list occupy a continuum between fact and myth. Some, such as <a href="http://www.macroevolution.net/pig-primate-hybrids.html" title="Read about pig-human hybrids">pig × human</a> or <a href="http://www.macroevolution.net/cow-human-hybrids.html" title="Read about cow-human hybrids">cow × human</a> are quite well documented. Others, at the other end of the spectrum, such as <a href="http://www.macroevolution.net/turtle-human-hybrid.html" title="Read about turtle-human hybrids">turtle × human</a> and <a href="http://www.macroevolution.net/human-seal-hybrids.html" title="Read about a seal-human hybrids">human × seal</a> can perhaps best be interpreted as myth. 
</p>
<p> 
<a href="http://www.macroevolution.net/very-strange-hybrids.html" title="Read about some very strange hybrids">Very strange hybrids >></a> 
</p>
<p>
